# Frontend Conventions

## Angular SPA

The frontend is built with **Angular** and served as a single-page application (SPA).

**Frontend location:** `frontend/`

**Build output:** `frontend/dist/browser/`

## JavaScript

**No inline scripts.** All JavaScript in external `.js` files:

```html
<!-- Good -->
<script src="{% static 'js/main.js' %}" defer></script>

<!-- Bad -->
<script>
  document.querySelector('.btn').addEventListener('click', ...)
</script>
```

**Use `defer` attribute** for non-blocking loading.

**Toggle classes, don't manipulate styles:**

```javascript
// Good
element.classList.add('hidden');
element.classList.remove('active');
element.classList.toggle('expanded');

// Bad
element.style.display = 'none';
element.style.backgroundColor = 'red';
```

## CSS

**No inline styles.** Use CSS classes:

```html
<!-- Good -->
<button class="btn btn-primary hidden">Click me</button>

<!-- Bad -->
<button style="display: none; background: blue;">Click me</button>
```

**Static files location:** `frontend/src/styles.scss` and component-specific styles

## Django Templates

**Minimal templates:** Only `templates/index.html` for Angular SPA catch-all route.

All UI is handled by Angular components in `frontend/src/app/`.

## Angular Patterns

**Component-based architecture:**
- Components in `frontend/src/app/features/`
- Services in `frontend/src/app/core/services/`
- Models/types in `frontend/src/app/core/api/`

**API Integration:**
- Django Ninja REST API at `/api/v1/`
- Auto-generated TypeScript client from OpenAPI schema
- Client code in `frontend/src/app/core/api/client/`

## Material Design

The project uses Angular Material:
- Components: `@angular/material`
- Icons: `@angular/material/icons`
- Theming: Custom theme in `frontend/src/styles.scss`

## PWA Support

Progressive Web App features:
- Service worker (via `@angular/pwa`)
- Web manifest (`manifest.webmanifest`)
- Offline support
- Installable app
